text.__SUMMARY__: The European white elm Ulmus laevis var. simplicidens exists at the National Botanic Garden of Latvia in Salaspils; it was obtained from St. Petersburg, Russia, in 1964.
text.Description: The tree was described by Egbert Wolf in 1924. The varietal epithet simplicidens translates as 'simple teeth'.
text.Accessions-Europe:
National Botanic Garden of Latvia, Salaspils, Latvia. Acc. no. 18137
